                    oc:sectionOrder 4 ;
                    oc:sectionTitle "When to Use" ],
                [ a oc:Section ;
                    oc:hasContent [ a oc:Paragraph ;
                            oc:blockType "paragraph" ;
                            oc:contentOrder 2 ;
                            oc:textContent "**Core principle:** ALWAYS find root cause before attempting fixes. Symptom fixes are failure." ],
                        [ a oc:Paragraph ;
                            oc:blockType "paragraph" ;
                            oc:contentOrder 1 ;
                            oc:textContent "Random fixes waste time and create new bugs. Quick patches mask underlying issues." ],
                        [ a oc:Paragraph ;
                            oc:blockType "paragraph" ;
                            oc:contentOrder 3 ;
                            oc:textContent "**Violating the letter of this process is violating the spirit of debugging.**" ] ;
                    oc:sectionLevel 2 ;
                    oc:sectionOrder 2 ;
                    oc:sectionTitle "Overview" ],
                [ a oc:Section ;
                    oc:hasContent [ a oc:Table ;
                            oc:blockType "table" ;
                            oc:contentOrder 1 ;
                            oc:rowCount 8 ;
                            oc:tableCaption "## Common Rationalizations" ;
                            oc:tableMarkdown """| Excuse | Reality |
|--------|---------|
| "Issue is simple, don't need process" | Simple issues have root causes too. Process is fast for simple bugs. |
| "Emergency, no time for process" | Systematic debugging is FASTER than guess-and-check thrashing. |
| "Just try this first, then investigate" | First fix sets the pattern. Do it right from the start. |
| "I'll write test after confirming fix works" | Untested fixes don't stick. Test first proves it. |
| "Multiple fixes at once saves time" | Can't isolate what worked. Causes new bugs. |
| "Reference too long, I'll adapt the pattern" | Partial understanding guarantees bugs. Read it completely. |
| "I see the problem, let me fix it" | Seeing symptoms ≠ understanding root cause. |
| "One more fix attempt" (after 2+ failures) | 3+ failures = architectural problem. Question pattern, don't fix again. |
""" ] ;
                    oc:sectionLevel 2 ;
                    oc:sectionOrder 12 ;
                    oc:sectionTitle "Common Rationalizations" ],
                [ a oc:Section ;
                    oc:hasContent [ a oc:Paragraph ;
                            oc:blockType "paragraph" ;
                            oc:contentOrder 1 ;
                            oc:textContent "From debugging sessions:" ],
                        [ a oc:BulletList ;
                            oc:blockType "bullet_list" ;
                            oc:contentOrder 2 ;
                            oc:hasItem [ a oc:BulletItem ;
                                    oc:blockType "bullet_item" ;
                                    oc:itemOrder 3 ;
                                    oc:itemText "First-time fix rate: 95% vs 40%" ],
                                [ a oc:BulletItem ;
                                    oc:blockType "bullet_item" ;
                                    oc:itemOrder 2 ;
                                    oc:itemText "Random fixes approach: 2-3 hours of thrashing" ],
                                [ a oc:BulletItem ;
                                    oc:blockType "bullet_item" ;
                                    oc:itemOrder 1 ;
                                    oc:itemText "Systematic approach: 15-30 minutes to fix" ],
                                [ a oc:BulletItem ;
                                    oc:blockType "bullet_item" ;
                                    oc:itemOrder 4 ;
                                    oc:itemText "New bugs introduced: Near zero vs common" ] ] ;
                    oc:sectionLevel 2 ;
                    oc:sectionOrder 16 ;
                    oc:sectionTitle "Real-World Impact" ],
                [ a oc:Section ;
                    oc:hasContent [ a oc:Paragraph ;
                            oc:blockType "paragraph" ;
                            oc:contentOrder 1 ;
                            oc:textContent "If you catch yourself thinking:" ],
